\q1
\v 29 So it is with the man who consorts with a married woman.
\q2 He shall not be held guiltless, nor anyone who touches her.
\q1
\v 30 It is not surprising if someone is caught stealing,
\q2 for he steals when he is hungry so that he may satisfy himself.
\q1
\v 31 But if he is caught, he shall repay sevenfold
\q2 and save himself by giving up all he possesses.
\q1
\v 32 The adulterer, through lack of sense,
\q2 brings destruction on his own soul.
\q1
\v 33 He endures pain and disgrace,
\q2 and that disgrace shall never be wiped away
\q1
\v 34 because the soul of her husband is filled with jealousy.
\q2 He will not show mercy on the day of vengeance;
\q1
\v 35 he will not let go of his hatred for any reason,
\q2 nor will he be reconciled by many gifts.
\c 7
\q1
\v 1 My son, guard my words
\q2 and hide away my commandments within you.
\c 8
\q1
\v 1 You shall preach wisdom
\q2 so that understanding may be yours to command,
\q1
\v 2 for she stands on high ground
\q2 and bestrides the centre of the road.
\q1
\v 3 She sits by the gates of princes
\q2 and sings at the doors, saying,
\q1
\v 4 ‘You men, I exhort you,
\q2 I raise my voice to the sons of men.
\q1
\v 5 You simple, understand subtlety;
\q2 and you who are untaught, take heart.
\q1
\v 6 Listen to me, for I will talk of solemn things
\q2 and my lips will speak of what is right.
\q1
\v 7 My mouth shall speak truth,
